title: Grateful Dead Live at Sam Boyd Silver Bowl on 1994-06-26
lineage: Dat (Sony PCM-R500) > Sound Devices 744T > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, Peggy-O, Minglewood Blues, Ramble On Rose, El Paso, So Many Roads, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Victim Or The Crime-> Eyes Of The World-> Box Of Rain, Saint Of Circumstance-> Terrapin Station >, Drums-> Space-> The Wheel-> All Along The Watchtower-> Morning Dew, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Traffic was on the bill for these shows, so the Dead turned up ready to play. 

Set 1 Highlights: El Paso, Tom Thumb's Blues! Decent TMNS jam. 

Set 2 HIGHlights: Very cool Victim. Check out that into and outro jam into Eyes though. Box is great, but Saint of Circumstance might be the best I've heard in '94. Jerry nails the solo. Casually slips into a 23 minute Terrapin (that sadly has some timing issues; the outro jam also isn't as creative as other dates in '94). Nice Drums>Space>Wheel. Dew is Dew.
